are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 4659, "bill_version_id": 2437, "bill_version": "Senate Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2008-02-04T13:40:52.01-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to provide for a jury trial in forfeiture proceedings. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 34-20B-88 be amended to read as follows: 34-20B-88. If a verified answer is filed, the forfeiture proceedings shall be set for hearing a trial on a day not more than sixty days therefrom; at from the date of the filing. Any party may demand a trial by jury for the forfeiture proceedings pursuant to subsection 15-6-38(b). At the hearing trial , the state shall establish probable cause for instituting the forfeiture action following which any owner, party in interest , or claimant who has filed a verified answer shall have has the burden of proving that the property seized is not subject to forfeiture under this chapter. If the court or a jury finds that the property is not subject to forfeiture under this chapter, the court shall order the property released to the owner, party in interest , or claimant as his according to such person's right, title , or interest appears; the . The court shall order the property forfeited if it the court or a jury determines that such property was subject to forfeiture. 250 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.04 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 4659, "bill_version_id": 2896, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2008-02-11T14:48:00.937-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 4659, "action_date": "2008-01-08T12:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 563, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/563.pdf", "status_text": "First r